Item 1. Business
Tesla, Inc. designs, develops, manufactures, leases, and sells electric vehicles, and energy generation and storage systems in the United States, China, and internationally. The company operates in two segments: Automotive, and Energy Generation and Storage.

sections.content:
Production scaling challenges and supply chain constraints.

Regulatory scrutiny on Autopilot and FSD features.
CEO reputational risk and distraction.
Additional general economic risks including inflation and interest rates.
